cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the methodological weaknesses and distortions in university performance rankings based on a selected subset of products, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are likely because the paper deals with research quality evaluation and assessment exercises. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant because the paper discusses bibliometrics and ranking methods. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are less likely but still possible because the paper may touch on issues related to security and machine learning in research evaluation.
